d 'BMC': module to Automatically Generate Chapter Configuration Text Files for Academic Monograph
d
d	 The bmc command is used to automatically generate
d configuration text files for each chapter of academic   
d monographs. Based on user-input chapter information, the command
d generates standardized bmc#.txt files    containing detailed
d instructions for seven tasks including chapter content
d development, LaTeX document	 generation, teaching plan
d creation, slide design, and case study writing.    The generated
d configuration files follow a standard format and can be used for
d automated document generation    workflows. This is particularly
d useful for academic writing projects that require batch
d processing of    multiple chapters. The version 2.7 adds a
d monograph() option to customize the academic monograph title,   
d allowing users to generate configuration files for different
d monograph projects. 
d
d KW: text management
d
d Requires: Stata version 16
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260504
d
